LVIV, Ukraine, March 15 (Reuters) - Ukraine raised 5.4 billion hryvnias ($185 million) on Tuesday at a third auction of local one-year bonds to raise money for its fight against Russian forces, the finance ministry said in a statement. After Russia invaded Ukraine on Feb. 24, the Ukrainian government said it hoped to raise about $1.36 billion through new hryvnia bond issues. ($1 = 29.2500 hryvnias) Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.